column5: MB2 those are some nice fish. Must be sweet living close to the river!  BlueEye that's awesome!! Good looking musky too.

sick with the flu right now. Super bummer as I have a fishing trip planned. I hope I can still get out.  But in lew(sarc) I found some old pics I thought id share. Most are fishing, others just great times.  I wouldnt normally do this but reports seem slow and im sure some pics help out!  Fall RR walleye on a blue jig    RR again through the ice in my old shack that some druggies destroyed    Nice eater   Another. Bray killed it that day. He caught 15 or so   43" inch pike if I remember correctly? I caught this fish twice. It broke me off so I had to switch rods. It at a berkely chigger craw    Thats a nickle! Even with the crap hold lol    Brays pb walleye a few years back

Fall fatty. 28"   The day I discovered bass spinnerbaits work on walleye!    Healthy fish!    This day was epic! Big eyes all day!      Rhetts pb walleye  Walleye naked   14" slab on big sawbill   Wifey! The best catch of all!!!!

More spinnerbait walleye   This girl was ThICk!!!    Spinner strikes again! Really urge anglers to try this method   Ninabutt used to join me all the time! Now she likes boys?    Memories     Clean walleye   Those guys in the boat were mad at me hahaha   Too big too eat
Shakeyhead walleye        Probably the smallest of the day hahaha      Fish on!!!  Boooooom!     Eater

Jigs pb northern    That cast though?    Camp lunch      Bonfires are a must!   Airtime in a break from icefishing    Nishnabe???   No rods allowed! Black sturgeon canooing     Ya might recognize this guy!     Long sault with limeyangler    3 time derby winner?    Lily was in her belly! Houseboat trip on LOTWs     Mainville limits
See yas on the other side?  Enjoy your kiddos, wife, nature!!!

Got out a couple weeks ago with my daughter in much warmer weather than today up north on the St. Lawrence. I'm an avid musky angler and member of Muskies Canada, Ganaoque Chapter.  It was pretty cool getting to fish with both my dad and my daughter on the same trip.  Ended up boating a couple nice muskies but my 3-year old daughter stole the show when she landed her first ever musky!  I hooked the fish, adjusted drag slightly and handed the rod over to Charlotte.  She laid rod flat on gun rail of boat and cranked her trophy in.  She got to catch the first skiâ€™ of her life and was soooooo happy!  Proud daddy moment there  If you look close in the picture, you can see 1.) the diaper I changed on my other daughter 2 casts before catching that musky  and 2.)  A lamprey that was on the fish.  This was the first ever lamprey I've seen on a musky before.  A quick picture and Charlotte helped me release the fish.  The fish kicked hard away and splashed us both.  My daughter now calls all fish larger than a sunfish a "Muskie".  We will work more on species identification once she turns 4 years old
^^^ now thats a great story/photo!!!  EPiC  Thanks for sharing!!!
